                <h2 class="subheading">How to Check RC (Registration Certificate) Online</h2>
                <p>RC (Registration Certificate) is proof that your vehicle is legally registered with the RTO.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Using VAHAN/Parivahan Portal:</h3>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Steps:</span></p>
                <ol>
                    <li> Go to <a href="https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/" class="for-link">https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/</a></li>
                    <li> Click on Informational Services then click on "Know Your Vehicle Details"</li>
                    <li> Create Account / Login (Enter Mobile Number & Verification Code & Captcha)</li>
                    <li> Enter your <span class="font-weight-700">vehicle registration number</span> (e.g., MH12AB1234)</li>
                    <li> Submit the <span class="font-weight-700">captcha code</span></li>
                    <li> View RC details: Owner name (masked), vehicle class, registration date, fuel type, fitness, and expiry</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="subheading">Using mParivahan App:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li> Install from Google Play or App Store</li>
                    <li> Open and enter vehicle number</li>
                    <li> Save vehicle under "My Garage"</li>
                    <li> Access RC details instantly</li>
                </ol>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Tip:</span> Use the app offline once the vehicle is added.</p>

